Align":139},[2039],{"text":2040,"type":75},"Real-Time Visibility and Workflow Automation",{"type":66,"content":2042},[2043],{"type":112,"attrs":2044,"content":2045},{"textAlign":139},[2046],{"text":2047,"type":75,"marks":2048},"Our solution provides real-time visibility of all assets and goods from arrival to departure. It automates critical workflows, manages spotter vehicles, and helps plan shipments and appointments.",[2049],{"type":149,"attrs":2050},{"color":708},{"id":2052,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2053,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2054,"is_external_url":49},91036990733742,"/storyblok/f/337048/1272x1196/29dcba4210/yard.png",{},{"value":2056},"#c2c2c2",{"label":2030,"link":2058},{"url":18,"cached_url":194},{"tab_label":2060,"title":2061,"description":2068,"background_image":2088,"background_color":2092,"button":2094},"AT THE DOCK",{"type":66,"content":2062},[2063],{"type":112,"attrs":2064,"content":2065},{"textAlign":139},[2066],{"text":2067,"type":75},"Optimize Loading and Improve Dock Efficiency",{"type":66,"content":2069},[2070],{"type":112,"attrs":2071,"content":2072},{"textAlign":139},[2073,2078,2083],{"text":2074,"type":75,"marks":2075},"YOS",[2076],{"type":149,"attrs":2077},{"color":708},{"text":1366,"type":75,"marks":2079},[2080,2082],{"type":149,"attrs":2081},{"color":708},{"type":1371},{"text":2084,"type":75,"marks":2085},"  streamlines loading and monitoring by integrating with your Warehouse Management System (WMS) to synchronize dock schedules with real-time yard activity. It offers a clear view of all incoming and outgoing shipments, helps manage dock door availability, and allows for pre-planning to reduce wait times.",[2086],{"type":149,"attrs":2087},{"color":708},{"id":2089,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2090,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2091,"is_external_url":49},113821374604331,"/storyblok/f/337048/565x336/e5f3b11568/dock-doors.png",{},{"value":2093},"#052424",{"label":2030,"link":2095},{"url":18,"cached_url":203},{"tab_label":2097,"title":2098,"description":2105,"background_image":2115,"background_color":2119,"button":2120},"ACROSS OPERATIONS",{"type":66,"content":2099},[2100],{"type":112,"attrs":2101,"content":2102},{"textAlign":139},[2103],{"text":2104,"type":75},"A Unified, Connected Data-Driven System",{"type":66,"content":2106},[2107],{"type":112,"attrs":2108,"content":2109},{"textAlign":139},[2110],{"text":2111,"type":75,"marks":2112},"From gate to dock and beyond, our system offers a cohesive platform that optimizes workflows and provides maximum visibility across all your yards. It delivers real-time insights and analytics through custom dashboards and alerts, helping you make data-driven decisions.",[2113],{"type":149,"attrs":2114},{"color":708},{"id":2116,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2117,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2118,"is_external_url":49},110544897979801,"/storyblok/f/337048/2034x1150/c561abc6ba/r.webp",{},{"value":2028},{"label":2030,"link":2121},{"url":18,"cached_url":211},[2123,2468,2514],{"name":2124,"created_at":2125,"published_at":2126,"updated_at":2127,"id":2128,"uuid":1769,"content":2129,"slug":2455,"full_slug":2456,"sort_by_date":139,"position":2457,"tag_list":2458,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2464,"meta_data":139,"group_id":2465,"first_published_at":2466,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":2467,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"If trust in freight is dead, why is it still running the yard?","2026-06-17T23:32:37.997Z","2026-06-17T23:46:56.455Z","2026-06-17T23:46:56.471Z",188618989585127,{"_uid":2130,"body":2131,"link":2438,"title":2124,"author":2439,"excerpt":2441,"category":2442,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2443,"seo_image":2444,"seo_title":2446,"button_text":132,"cover_image":2447,"gated_asset":2451,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":2452,"background_color":2453,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"2e214bba-8b06-4181-85d1-edd14859a052",{"type":66,"content":2132},[2133,2142,2150,2230,2238,2246,2254,2262,2270,2278,2286,2294,2302,2310,2318,2326,2334,2342,2350,2358,2366,2374,2382,2390,2398,2406,2414,2422,2430],{"type":112,"attrs":2134,"content":2135},{"textAlign":139},[2136],{"text":2137,"type":75,"marks":2138},"I’ve been in the supply chain industry for 30 years. For the past decade or so, as new software solutions flooded the market, anyone who knew “how things really operated,” knew it was an industry run on relationships. Technology was just a supplement to how money, data and freight got moved from A to B. Even with our current AI gold rush, there are still industry veterans who remember faxing bills of lading and are still working with those same colleagues. I’d argue the foundation of the industry – trust, mutual respect, familiarity – has eroded to a point of no return. Not because of technology, but because of prolific freight fraud that has fostered a culture of paranoia across the industry. And as a veteran of yard technology and systems, I can tell you a lot of this distrust starts in the yard. ",[2139],{"type":149,"attrs":2140},{"color":2141},"#000000",{"type":112,"attrs":2143,"content":2144},{"textAlign":139},[2145],{"text":2146,"type":75,"marks":2147},"Walk into almost any logistics facility in the country and you'll find the same scene at the gate: a person with a tablet or a clipboard. They typically don’t have any information on the trucks coming in – is this the carrier we booked? Is this driver legit? Is that the right trailer, sealed the way it left the last yard? Security and visibility solutions have helped operators answer those questions across almost every node of the supply chain, but in the yard, carrier verification and security is about as sophisticated as the check out process at Costco. ",[2148],{"type":149,"attrs":2149},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2151,"content":2152},{"textAlign":139},[2153,2158,2170,2175,2184,2189,2197,2202,2211,2216,2225],{"text":2154,"type":75,"marks":2155},"Cargo theft across the U.S. and Canada ",[2156],{"type":149,"attrs":2157},{"color":2141},{"text":2159,"type":75,"marks":2160},"climbed past $725 million last year",[2161,2165,2168],{"type":2162,"attrs":2163},"link",{"href":2164,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.cargonet.com/news-and-events/cargonet-in-the-media/2025-theft-trends/",{"type":149,"attrs":2166},{"color":2167},"#1155CC",{"type":2169},"underline",{"text":2171,"type":75,"marks":2172},", a 60% jump, and the fastest-growing vector isn't the smash-and-grab. It's ",[2173],{"type":149,"attrs":2174},{"color":2141},{"text":2176,"type":75,"marks":2177},"fraud",[2178,2181,2183],{"type":2162,"attrs":2179},{"href":2180,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.ic3.gov/PSA/2026/PSA260430",{"type":149,"attrs":2182},{"color":2167},{"type":2169},{"text":2185,"type":75,"marks":2186},": fictitious pickups, stolen identities, carriers that look legitimate on a load board and vanish with a full trailer. The FBI has ",[2187],{"type":149,"attrs":2188},{"color":2141},{"text":2190,"type":75,"marks":2191},"said plainly",[2192,2194,2196],{"type":2162,"attrs":2193},{"href":2180,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},{"type":149,"attrs":2195},{"color":2167},{"type":2169},{"text":2198,"type":75,"marks":2199}," that impersonation is now the dominant way freight gets stolen. And people like the veteran gate guard who knew every regular driver by name is retiring. ",[2200],{"type":149,"attrs":2201},{"color":2141},{"text":2203,"type":75,"marks":2204},"Warehouse turnover sits near 50%",[2205,2208,2210],{"type":2162,"attrs":2206},{"href":2207,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.bls.gov/news.release/pdf/jolts.pdf",{"type":149,"attrs":2209},{"color":2167},{"type":2169},{"text":2212,"type":75,"marks":2213},"; for long-haul drivers it's",[2214],{"type":149,"attrs":2215},{"color":2141},{"text":2217,"type":75,"marks":2218}," above 90%",[2219,2222,2224],{"type":2162,"attrs":2220},{"href":2221,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.ooida.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The-Churn-A-Brief-Look-at-the-Roots-of-High-Driver-Turnover-in-U.S.-Trucking.pdf",{"type":149,"attrs":2223},{"color":2167},{"type":2169},{"text":2226,"type":75,"marks":2227},". ",[2228],{"type":149,"attrs":2229},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2231,"content":2232},{"textAlign":139},[2233],{"text":2234,"type":75,"marks":2235},"So we have a place where every load in the supply chain physically changes hands, where legal custody transfers, where accurate information is scarce or absent, where information asymmetry is accelerating fraud, and where the human safety net is thinning. And it remains the one part of the chain we never really invested in. Go figure. ",[2236],{"type":149,"attrs":2237},{"color":2141},{"type":69,"attrs":2239,"content":2240},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2241],{"text":2242,"type":75,"marks":2243},"Yard security is, in fact, the warehouse’s problem ",[2244],{"type":149,"attrs":2245},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2247,"content":2248},{"textAlign":139},[2249],{"text":2250,"type":75,"marks":2251},"When a load is stolen through fraud, the strategic theft completes at the moment the trailer is released. The facility that released it is the one left holding the liability. The contractual and compliance obligations that increasingly govern freight (documented carrier vetting, verified driver identity, conveyance inspection, an unbroken chain-of-custody record) all point back to the gate that let the truck through.",[2252],{"type":149,"attrs":2253},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2255,"content":2256},{"textAlign":139},[2257],{"text":2258,"type":75,"marks":2259},"Today, cargo insurers, customer contracts, and programs like CTPAT increasingly demand records that paper-based yards cannot produce, and that a gate workforce turning over every eighteen months cannot reliably capture by hand. Yard security is, in fact, the warehouse’s problem, and it has to be solved at the gate, inside the system that runs it, because that's where custody actually changes and where the record either gets made or gets lost.",[2260],{"type":149,"attrs":2261},{"color":2141},{"type":69,"attrs":2263,"content":2264},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2265],{"text":2266,"type":75,"marks":2267},"No one owns the yard (and that’s a problem)",[2268],{"type":149,"attrs":2269},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2271,"content":2272},{"textAlign":139},[2273],{"text":2274,"type":75,"marks":2275},"I got my first IT job at a 3PL in the early 1990s. It's tempting to say the yard security problem is about bad software, that the industry tried to secure the yard and the tools weren't good enough. But back then the operations team was more worried about people jumping the fence, cutting the seal, and throwing product back over. Technology wasn't available, so companies threw bodies at it.",[2276],{"type":149,"attrs":2277},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2279,"content":2280},{"textAlign":139},[2281],{"text":2282,"type":75,"marks":2283},"Yard management software was built for operations and throughput: dock assignments, dwell time, trailer locations, getting trucks in and out efficiently. Security, identity, and chain of custody were understood as separate concerns, owned by separate people, and addressed, when they were addressed at all, by separate means. This is why most facilities outsource the gate to a security company. Some of it got handled by point solutions bolted on from the outside: carrier-vetting services, cameras, physical ID checks by a guy named Steve. A lot of it wasn't handled by software at all.",[2284],{"type":149,"attrs":2285},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2287,"content":2288},{"textAlign":139},[2289],{"text":2290,"type":75,"marks":2291},"The result is a set of capabilities that have always lived in paper documentation and verbal communication over a radio – silos – disconnected from each other and from the system that actually runs the yard. For example, the camera never knew who the driver was, the carrier check never reached the gate, and the custody record, where it existed, sat in a binder. None of these pieces were wrong on their own. They simply were never brought together, because for most of the industry's history there was no obvious reason to make changes. ",[2292],{"type":149,"attrs":2293},{"color":2141},{"type":69,"attrs":2295,"content":2296},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2297],{"text":2298,"type":75,"marks":2299},"The lesser of two evils",[2300],{"type":149,"attrs":2301},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2303,"content":2304},{"textAlign":139},[2305],{"text":2306,"type":75,"marks":2307},"For most of its history, buying yard technology meant choosing between two unsatisfying options, and the choice had nothing to do with security. It was just the shape of the market.",[2308],{"type":149,"attrs":2309},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2311,"content":2312},{"textAlign":139},[2313],{"text":2314,"type":75,"marks":2315},"The first option was the large enterprise platform that promised end-to-end control of everything. In practice it was a clunky, glorified system of record: an expensive license, a six month deployment, zero flexibility. It promised comprehensive coverage yet could not change with the business without a massive change request and a matching invoice. You got breadth, and you paid for it in cost and rigidity.",[2316],{"type":149,"attrs":2317},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2319,"content":2320},{"textAlign":139},[2321],{"text":2322,"type":75,"marks":2323},"The second was the point solution, with the opposite promise: do one thing exceptionally well. Many genuinely deliver. But when every capability comes from a different vendor, the buyer inherits subscriptions, logins, dashboards, data formats, and renewal cycles, none of which speak to one another. Someone has to integrate them, monitor them, reconcile their outputs, and re-buy them every year. You got depth, and you paid for it in fragmentation.",[2324],{"type":149,"attrs":2325},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2327,"content":2328},{"textAlign":139},[2329],{"text":2330,"type":75,"marks":2331},"So that was the trade. Breadth or depth. One expensive, rigid system or ten sharp tools that don't talk. For decades there was no third answer, and no reason to expect one.",[2332],{"type":149,"attrs":2333},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2335,"content":2336},{"textAlign":139},[2337],{"text":2338,"type":75,"marks":2339},"AI-native development is the third answer. Capabilities that once demanded a specialized enterprise stack and a year of integration can now be built and deployed in a fraction of the time, at a fraction of the cost. You no longer choose between breadth and depth, or between flexibility and cohesion. You can have technology that does many things at once, changes with the business, and doesn't break the bank or trigger a year of change management.",[2340],{"type":149,"attrs":2341},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2343,"content":2344},{"textAlign":139},[2345],{"text":2346,"type":75,"marks":2347},"That is what makes this moment matter for the yard. Once the tradeoff collapses, capabilities that used to demand entirely separate systems can finally live in one. And the two that most need to come together are yard management and yard security, domains that were always treated as separate concerns, owned by separate people, bought from separate vendors. For the first time, there is no reason they have to be.",[2348],{"type":149,"attrs":2349},{"color":2141},{"type":69,"attrs":2351,"content":2352},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2353],{"text":2354,"type":75,"marks":2355},"Security should live inside the system already running the gate ",[2356],{"type":149,"attrs":2357},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2359,"content":2360},{"textAlign":139},[2361],{"text":2362,"type":75,"marks":2363},"For the first time, the technology exists to create a modular layer inside the system that already runs the yard. The capabilities that secure a yard (knowing the carrier, verifying the driver, watching the perimeter, documenting what actually leaves) no longer have to be a stack of disconnected point tools or a separate enterprise security program.",[2364],{"type":149,"attrs":2365},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2367,"content":2368},{"textAlign":139},[2369],{"text":2370,"type":75,"marks":2371},"We’re seeing a great convergence: yard security and yard management becoming one single entity. And AI has made it feasible to build something modular and affordable that does both at once.",[2372],{"type":149,"attrs":2373},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2375,"content":2376},{"textAlign":139},[2377],{"text":2378,"type":75,"marks":2379},"Secondarily, we’re able to address both yard security and management because the data is the same data. For example, the check-in event and the security event are not two events; they are one event seen from two angles. The instant a truck reaches the gate, the system logging it for operations already holds nearly everything security needs, such as who is driving, what they are hauling, what the camera sees, and exactly when it happened. Recording that as an operations entry over here and a security entry over there was never a principle of good design.",[2380],{"type":149,"attrs":2381},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2383,"content":2384},{"textAlign":139},[2385],{"text":2386,"type":75,"marks":2387},"Security should live inside the system already running the gate.",[2388],{"type":149,"attrs":2389},{"color":2141},{"type":69,"attrs":2391,"content":2392},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2393],{"text":2394,"type":75,"marks":2395},"Convergence",[2396],{"type":149,"attrs":2397},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2399,"content":2400},{"textAlign":139},[2401],{"text":2402,"type":75,"marks":2403},"Convergence matters because disconnected tools produce alerts, and unified systems produce decisions. A carrier-risk flag in one inbox, an ID scan in another, and a camera feed in a third are three pieces of information someone might later assemble into a conclusion, usually after the truck is already gone. That is retroactive security. It documents how the goods were lost.",[2404],{"type":149,"attrs":2405},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2407,"content":2408},{"textAlign":139},[2409],{"text":2410,"type":75,"marks":2411},"A fraudulent carrier at the gate is a decision that has to be made before the arm lifts. It can only be made if the carrier check, the driver's identity, the appointment, and the camera feed are all the same conversation, in the same place, at the same time. That is the entire point of bringing these capabilities together. Convergence isn't about owning fewer vendors, though you will. It's about turning a pile of after-the-fact records into a decision made at the only moment a decision still matters.",[2412],{"type":149,"attrs":2413},{"color":2141},{"type":69,"attrs":2415,"content":2416},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2417],{"text":2418,"type":75,"marks":2419},"The yard has always been the supply chain’s soft spot",[2420],{"type":149,"attrs":2421},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2423,"content":2424},{"textAlign":139},[2425],{"text":2426,"type":75,"marks":2427},"To be clear, there’s always been freight fraud and the yard was always the soft spot. It’s because it’s where custody is most exposed. What's new is that the excuse is gone and the stakes are higher. Solutions exist that will allow, for the first time, the facility that released the load to prove who took it, prove they were authorized to, and prove that what was left matched what was supposed to. ",[2428],{"type":149,"attrs":2429},{"color":2141},{"type":112,"attrs":2431,"content":2432},{"textAlign":139},[2433],{"text":2434,"type":75,"marks":2435},"That is what this moment in technology actually offers logistics. To give the yard the same visibility and accountability the rest of the supply chain has taken for granted for years.",[2436],{"type":149,"attrs":2437},{"color":2141},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[2440],"4970a15a-a518-4e01-a0de-cb3b272e0fe4","Cargo fraud has made the yard the supply chain's most exposed point, yet yard security and yard management have always been treated as separate problems bought from separate vendors. Terminal's argument: AI-native development has collapsed that tradeoff, making it possible for the first time to converge both into one system at the gate, where custody actually changes and the decision to lift the arm still matters","blog","Post",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2445},{},"Why Yard Security Belongs Inside Your Yard Management System",{"id":2448,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2449,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2450,"is_external_url":49},188621303706158,"/storyblok/f/337048/800x533/789821de04/yard-gate.jpg",{},[],"Freight fraud made the yard the supply chain's soft spot. See why AI-native systems can finally converge yard security and management at the gate, where it counts.",{"value":2028,"plugin":2454},"storyblok-palette","if-trust-in-freight-is-dead-why-is-it-still-running-the-yard-","all-resources/if-trust-in-freight-is-dead-why-is-it-still-running-the-yard-",-2310,[2459,2460,2461,2462,2463],"ai","chain of custody","Logistics Technology ","security","yms",80887824638261,"3f685df9-91c4-4a64-9531-e80ac5078855","2026-06-17T23:36:58.081Z",[],{"name":2469,"created_at":2470,"published_at":2471,"updated_at":2472,"id":2473,"uuid":1770,"content":2474,"slug":2507,"full_slug":2508,"sort_by_date":139,"position":2509,"tag_list":2510,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2464,"meta_data":139,"group_id":2511,"first_published_at":2512,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":2513,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"Gate Entry - Computer Vision ","2025-10-01T14:24:33.651Z","2026-03-10T17:03:26.740Z","2026-03-10T17:03:26.752Z",96825645711889,{"_uid":2475,"body":2476,"link":2496,"title":2469,"author":2497,"excerpt":2469,"category":2499,"subtitle":18,"component":2443,"seo_image":2500,"seo_title":18,"button_text":912,"cover_image":2502,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":18,"background_color":2506},"cb11d1b7-c3ab-4f89-889f-698ea962bb3b",{"type":66,"content":2477},[2478,2482,2491],{"type":112,"attrs":2479,"content":2480},{"textAlign":139},[2481],{"text":103,"type":75},{"type":2483,"attrs":2484},"blok",{"id":2485,"body":2486},"0c36f4a3-0155-48a1-8e5f-7f225e257603",[2487],{"url":2488,"_uid":2489,"title":18,"caption":18,"component":2490},"https://youtu.be/hEVabsyiC-g?si=2r0x0X2KmKxSX1gs","i-d7b4cb03-997a-4b64-8d4c-b20e6ed3855b","VideoEmbed",{"type":112,"attrs":2492,"content":2493},{"textAlign":139},[2494],{"text":2495,"type":75},"Every second counts. Terminal computer vision gate workflows cut check-in times by up to 85%, without compromising security or accuracy. ",{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":96,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[2498],"489dfeeb-71d3-4812-95bb-a398f19766eb","video",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2501},{},{"id":2503,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2504,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2505,"is_external_url":49},96825834903865,"/storyblok/f/337048/2892x1594/059d3122cb/y.webp",{},{"value":2028,"plugin":2454},"gate-entry-computer-vision","all-resources/gate-entry-computer-vision",-930,[],"b4b26c87-3fc5-4232-9afe-a2545db6cd7d","2025-10-01T14:26:22.249Z",[],{"name":2515,"created_at":2516,"published_at":2517,"updated_at":2518,"id":2519,"uuid":1771,"content":2520,"slug":3176,"full_slug":3177,"sort_by_date":139,"position":3178,"tag_list":3179,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2464,"meta_data":139,"group_id":3183,"first_published_at":3184,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":3185,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"Gate Automation Systems: Boost Security & Efficiency Today","2025-09-18T09:16:45.698Z","2026-03-27T17:58:59.082Z","2026-03-27T17:58:59.108Z",92149373761694,{"_uid":2521,"body":2522,"link":3162,"title":2515,"author":3163,"excerpt":3165,"category":2442,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2443,"seo_image":3166,"seo_title":3168,"button_text":132,"cover_image":3169,"gated_asset":3173,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":3174,"background_color":3175,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"2112bad4-a2e3-4e81-a3a2-8a4a6a241dfc",{"type":66,"content":2523},[2524,2535,2547,2556,2613,2618,2625,2630,2637,2642,2665,2670,2677,2682,2698,2703,2710,2719,2724,2731,2736,2741,2748,2755,2764,2769,2780,2787,2797,2802,2807,2814,2819,2824,2829,2836,2841,2846,2872,2879,2884,2889,2919,2924,2931,2936,2941,2948,2959,2964,2973,2980,2989,3035,3042,3051,3056,3102,3109,3119,3124,3129,3136,3152,3157],{"type":112,"attrs":2525,"content":2526},{"textAlign":139},[2527,2529,2533],{"text":2528,"type":75},"A ",{"text":2530,"type":75,"marks":2531},"gate automation system",[2532],{"type":710},{"text":2534,"type":75}," is a technology that turns traditional manual entry points into smart, self-operating access controls. It combines hardware like automated barriers, sensors, and cameras with advanced software to manage vehicle and personnel entry without the need for human involvement.",{"type":112,"attrs":2536,"content":2538},{"textAlign":2537},"left",[2539,2541,2545],{"text":2540,"type":75},"Modern logistics and industrial facilities rely heavily on ",{"text":2542,"type":75,"marks":2543},"automated gate control",[2544],{"type":710},{"text":2546,"type":75}," solutions to handle the large number of goods and vehicles that pass through every day. With over $50 billion worth of goods moving through more than 50,000 warehouses and factories in North America daily, relying on manual gate operations can cause significant delays throughout the entire supply chain. What you need are systems that can efficiently handle high volumes of traffic while ensuring security and maintaining visibility into operations.",{"type":112,"attrs":2548,"content":2549},{"textAlign":2537},[2550,2554],{"text":2551,"type":75,"marks":2552},"Facility access management",[2553],{"type":710},{"text":2555,"type":75}," through manual processes comes with several operational challenges:",{"type":1544,"content":2557},[2558,2569,2580,2591,2602],{"type":1547,"content":2559},[2560],{"type":112,"attrs":2561,"content":2562},{"textAlign":139},[2563,2567],{"text":2564,"type":75,"marks":2565},"Long wait times",[2566],{"type":710},{"text":2568,"type":75}," during busy periods when security personnel have to manually check credentials and documents",{"type":1547,"content":2570},[2571],{"type":112,"attrs":2572,"content":2573},{"textAlign":139},[2574,2578],{"text":2575,"type":75,"marks":2576},"Mistakes made by humans",[2577],{"type":710},{"text":2579,"type":75}," in identifying vehicles and granting authorization",{"type":1547,"content":2581},[2582],{"type":112,"attrs":2583,"content":2584},{"textAlign":139},[2585,2589],{"text":2586,"type":75,"marks":2587},"Difficulty in scaling up",[2588],{"type":710},{"text":2590,"type":75}," when traffic volumes vary during different shifts",{"type":1547,"content":2592},[2593],{"type":112,"attrs":2594,"content":2595},{"textAlign":139},[2596,2600],{"text":2597,"type":75,"marks":2598},"Inconsistent data collection",[2599],{"type":710},{"text":2601,"type":75}," that leads to gaps in visibility and tracking within the yard",{"type":1547,"content":2603},[2604],{"type":112,"attrs":2605,"content":2606},{"textAlign":139},[2607,2611],{"text":2608,"type":75,"marks":2609},"Higher labor costs",[2610],{"type":710},{"text":2612,"type":75}," due to the need for continuous staffing",{"type":112,"attrs":2614,"content":2615},{"textAlign":2537},[2616],{"text":2617,"type":75},"The yard is an area in logistics operations where there is still a significant gap in data and technology. While warehouse management systems (WMS) and transportation management systems (TMS) have digitized other parts of the supply chain, gate automation systems fill this critical gap by bringing intelligence and automation to entry points where operational efficiency begins.",{"type":69,"attrs":2619,"content":2620},{"level":138,"textAlign":2537},[2621],{"text":2622,"type":75,"marks":2623},"Core Technologies Behind Gate Automation Systems",[2624],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2626,"content":2627},{"textAlign":2537},[2628],{"text":2629,"type":75},"Modern gate automation relies on a sophisticated blend of identification and tracking technologies that work together to create seamless entry and exit processes. Each technology brings unique capabilities and limitations that determine the effectiveness of your automated gate system.",{"type":69,"attrs":2631,"content":2632},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2633],{"text":2634,"type":75,"marks":2635},"RFID Technology for Vehicle Identification",[2636],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2638,"content":2639},{"textAlign":2537},[2640],{"text":2641,"type":75},"RFID technology forms the backbone of many automated gate systems through its ability to provide instant, contactless vehicle identification. You can deploy RFID tags on vehicles, trailers, or equipment, allowing readers positioned at gate entry points to automatically detect and authenticate assets as they approach.",{"type":1544,"content":2643},[2644,2651,2658],{"type":1547,"content":2645},[2646],{"type":112,"attrs":2647,"content":2648},{"textAlign":139},[2649],{"text":2650,"type":75},"The technology operates through radio frequency communication between tags and readers, enabling identification from distances of several feet without requiring direct line-of-sight contact.",{"type":1547,"content":2652},[2653],{"type":112,"attrs":2654,"content":2655},{"textAlign":139},[2656],{"text":2657,"type":75},"This capability proves particularly valuable in harsh weather conditions where visual identification methods might fail.",{"type":1547,"content":2659},[2660],{"type":112,"attrs":2661,"content":2662},{"textAlign":139},[2663],{"text":2664,"type":75},"RFID systems can store multiple data points including vehicle registration, driver information, cargo details, and authorization levels.",{"type":112,"attrs":2666,"content":2667},{"textAlign":2537},[2668],{"text":2669,"type":75},"However, RFID implementation requires pre-registration of all vehicles and regular tag maintenance. You'll need to manage tag replacement when they become damaged or lost, and ensure consistent tag placement across your fleet for reliable detection.",{"type":69,"attrs":2671,"content":2672},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2673],{"text":2674,"type":75,"marks":2675},"ANPR Systems and Their Operational Boundaries",[2676],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2678,"content":2679},{"textAlign":2537},[2680],{"text":2681,"type":75},"ANPR systems leverage optical character recognition to automatically read license plates from camera feeds, providing a non-intrusive identification method that doesn't require additional hardware on vehicles. These systems excel in environments where you need to identify unregistered or visiting vehicles that lack RFID tags.",{"type":1544,"content":2683},[2684,2691],{"type":1547,"content":2685},[2686],{"type":112,"attrs":2687,"content":2688},{"textAlign":139},[2689],{"text":2690,"type":75},"Modern ANPR technology can process multiple license plate formats and handle various lighting conditions through advanced image processing algorithms.",{"type":1547,"content":2692},[2693],{"type":112,"attrs":2694,"content":2695},{"textAlign":139},[2696],{"text":2697,"type":75},"The systems maintain databases of authorized plates and can instantly flag unauthorized vehicles or those on security watch lists.",{"type":112,"attrs":2699,"content":2700},{"textAlign":2537},[2701],{"text":2702,"type":75},"ANPR systems face challenges with dirty, damaged, or non-standard license plates. Weather conditions, camera positioning, and lighting quality directly impact recognition accuracy. You'll also encounter limitations when dealing with international plates or specialty vehicle registrations that don't conform to standard formatting.",{"type":69,"attrs":2704,"content":2705},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2706],{"text":2707,"type":75,"marks":2708},"GPS Integration for Enhanced Yard Management",[2709],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2711,"content":2712},{"textAlign":2537},[2713,2717],{"text":2714,"type":75,"marks":2715},"GPS tracking",[2716],{"type":710},{"text":2718,"type":75}," integration transforms gate automation from simple access control into comprehensive yard visibility. When combined with gate systems, GPS provides real-time location data that enables you to track vehicle movements from entry through exit, creating a complete audit trail of yard activities.",{"type":112,"attrs":2720,"content":2721},{"textAlign":2537},[2722],{"text":2723,"type":75},"This integration supports advanced yard management functions including automated parking assignments, route optimization within the facility, and precise dwell time calculations. You can monitor vehicle locations continuously, reducing asset search times and improving overall yard efficiency.",{"type":69,"attrs":2725,"content":2726},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2727],{"text":2728,"type":75,"marks":2729},"AI Vision Systems for Comprehensive Recognition",[2730],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2732,"content":2733},{"textAlign":2537},[2734],{"text":2735,"type":75},"AI vision systems represent the most advanced approach to gate automation, combining multiple recognition capabilities into unified platforms. These systems can simultaneously identify vehicles through license plates, recognize drivers through facial recognition, detect cargo configurations, and assess vehicle conditions.",{"type":112,"attrs":2737,"content":2738},{"textAlign":2537},[2739],{"text":2740,"type":75},"AI-powered solutions adapt to varying environmental conditions and learn from operational data to improve accuracy over time. You benefit from systems that can handle complex scenarios involving multiple vehicles, unusual cargo configurations, or non-standard identification requirements that would challenge traditional single-technology approaches.",{"type":69,"attrs":2742,"content":2743},{"level":138,"textAlign":2537},[2744],{"text":2745,"type":75,"marks":2746},"Enhancing Security and Operational Efficiency with Gate Automation",[2747],{"type":710},{"type":69,"attrs":2749,"content":2750},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2751],{"text":2752,"type":75,"marks":2753},"Automated Security Gates: A Game Changer for Entry Points",[2754],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2756,"content":2757},{"textAlign":2537},[2758,2762],{"text":2759,"type":75,"marks":2760},"Automated security gates",[2761],{"type":710},{"text":2763,"type":75}," are revolutionizing the way we secure our facilities. Gone are the days of relying solely on human guards to verify credentials. With automated gates, entry points become intelligent checkpoints that can authenticate vehicles with unmatched accuracy.",{"type":112,"attrs":2765,"content":2766},{"textAlign":2537},[2767],{"text":2768,"type":75},"These modern systems use advanced technology to cross-reference multiple data sources—such as RFID tags, license plates, and driver credentials—with authorized databases in real-time. This means that instead of relying on a guard's judgment or manual checks, every vehicle is verified against official records instantly.",{"type":112,"attrs":2770,"content":2771},{"textAlign":2537},[2772,2774,2778],{"text":2773,"type":75},"The result? An end to human error and a guarantee that only legitimate vehicles gain ",{"text":2775,"type":75,"marks":2776},"access control",[2777],{"type":710},{"text":2779,"type":75}," to your facility.",{"type":69,"attrs":2781,"content":2782},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2783],{"text":2784,"type":75,"marks":2785},"Strengthening Security Measures with Smart Barriers",[2786],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2788,"content":2789},{"textAlign":2537},[2790,2792,2796],{"text":2791,"type":75},"One of the key advantages of automated gates is their ability to integrate with identification technologies. This combination creates a powerful defense against ",{"text":2793,"type":75,"marks":2794},"unauthorized access prevention",[2795],{"type":710},{"text":1539,"type":75},{"type":112,"attrs":2798,"content":2799},{"textAlign":2537},[2800],{"text":2801,"type":75},"Here's how it works: smart barriers remain locked until all verification protocols confirm vehicle authorization. In other words, even if a driver presents valid credentials, the barrier will not open unless the system has also verified other factors such as the vehicle's license plate or RFID tag.",{"type":112,"attrs":2803,"content":2804},{"textAlign":2537},[2805],{"text":2806,"type":75},"This multi-layered approach adds an extra layer of security and ensures that even if one verification method fails, there are still other checks in place.",{"type":69,"attrs":2808,"content":2809},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2810],{"text":2811,"type":75,"marks":2812},"Tailoring Security Protocols for High-Value Loads",[2813],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2815,"content":2816},{"textAlign":2537},[2817],{"text":2818,"type":75},"Another benefit of gate automation is the flexibility it offers in configuring security protocols. You can customize these systems to require additional authentication for high-value or high-risk loads.",{"type":112,"attrs":2820,"content":2821},{"textAlign":2537},[2822],{"text":2823,"type":75},"For example, if a truck carrying expensive merchandise arrives at your facility, you can set up the system to trigger enhanced security measures automatically. This could include sending alerts to security personnel or requiring additional documentation from the driver.",{"type":112,"attrs":2825,"content":2826},{"textAlign":2537},[2827],{"text":2828,"type":75},"By tailoring your security protocols based on specific criteria, you can better protect your assets and mitigate potential risks.",{"type":69,"attrs":2830,"content":2831},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2832],{"text":2833,"type":75,"marks":2834},"Continuous Surveillance with Integrated Cameras",[2835],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2837,"content":2838},{"textAlign":2537},[2839],{"text":2840,"type":75},"In addition to automated barriers, many gate automation systems also come equipped with integrated security cameras. These cameras provide continuous surveillance at entry points and capture high-resolution footage of every vehicle interaction.",{"type":112,"attrs":2842,"content":2843},{"textAlign":2537},[2844],{"text":2845,"type":75},"The advantage of having video monitoring is twofold:",{"type":2847,"attrs":2848,"content":2849},"ordered_list",{"order":71},[2850,2861],{"type":1547,"content":2851},[2852],{"type":112,"attrs":2853,"content":2854},{"textAlign":139},[2855,2859],{"text":2856,"type":75,"marks":2857},"Deterrence against suspicious activities:",[2858],{"type":710},{"text":2860,"type":75}," Knowing that they are being recorded can discourage individuals from attempting unauthorized entries or engaging in illicit behavior.",{"type":1547,"content":2862},[2863],{"type":112,"attrs":2864,"content":2865},{"textAlign":139},[2866,2870],{"text":2867,"type":75,"marks":2868},"Evidence collection for investigations:",[2869],{"type":710},{"text":2871,"type":75}," In case an incident occurs—such as a theft or vandalism—the recorded footage can serve as valuable evidence during investigations.",{"type":69,"attrs":2873,"content":2874},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2875],{"text":2876,"type":75,"marks":2877},"Flagging Suspicious Activities Automatically",[2878],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2880,"content":2881},{"textAlign":2537},[2882],{"text":2883,"type":75},"To further enhance security monitoring capabilities, some advanced gate automation solutions have built-in intelligence that allows them to automatically flag suspicious activities.",{"type":112,"attrs":2885,"content":2886},{"textAlign":2537},[2887],{"text":2888,"type":75},"Here are some examples:",{"type":1544,"content":2890},[2891,2898,2905,2912],{"type":1547,"content":2892},[2893],{"type":112,"attrs":2894,"content":2895},{"textAlign":139},[2896],{"text":2897,"type":75},"Vehicles attempting multiple unauthorized entries",{"type":1547,"content":2899},[2900],{"type":112,"attrs":2901,"content":2902},{"textAlign":139},[2903],{"text":2904,"type":75},"Damaged or obscured license plates",{"type":1547,"content":2906},[2907],{"type":112,"attrs":2908,"content":2909},{"textAlign":139},[2910],{"text":2911,"type":75},"Personnel exiting vehicles in restricted areas",{"type":1547,"content":2913},[2914],{"type":112,"attrs":2915,"content":2916},{"textAlign":139},[2917],{"text":2918,"type":75},"Unusual traffic patterns during off-hours",{"type":112,"attrs":2920,"content":2921},{"textAlign":2537},[2922],{"text":2923,"type":75},"By identifying these potential threats proactively, you can take appropriate actions before any harm is done.",{"type":69,"attrs":2925,"content":2926},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2927],{"text":2928,"type":75,"marks":2929},"Seamless Integration with Existing Security Infrastructure",[2930],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2932,"content":2933},{"textAlign":2537},[2934],{"text":2935,"type":75},"Another advantage of integrated camera systems is their ability to work seamlessly with your existing security infrastructure. This means that if you already have surveillance cameras installed throughout your facility, you can easily connect them with the gate automation system.",{"type":112,"attrs":2937,"content":2938},{"textAlign":2537},[2939],{"text":2940,"type":75},"The integration creates a comprehensive monitoring network where all camera feeds are accessible from a central location. This makes it easier for security personnel to keep an eye on multiple areas",{"type":69,"attrs":2942,"content":2943},{"level":138,"textAlign":2537},[2944],{"text":2945,"type":75,"marks":2946},"Environmental, Cost, Integration Challenges, and Future Trends in Gate Automation Systems",[2947],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2949,"content":2950},{"textAlign":2537},[2951,2953,2957],{"text":2952,"type":75},"The environmental benefits of ",{"text":2954,"type":75,"marks":2955},"gate automation systems",[2956],{"type":710},{"text":2958,"type":75}," extend far beyond operational improvements. When vehicles spend less time idling at entry points, facilities experience significant emission reduction across their operations. Traditional manual check-in processes often require trucks to wait 15-30 minutes with engines running, contributing to unnecessary carbon emissions. Automated systems reduce this wait time to under 5 minutes, directly cutting fuel consumption and improving air quality around facility perimeters.",{"type":112,"attrs":2960,"content":2961},{"textAlign":2537},[2962],{"text":2963,"type":75},"However, it's not just about reducing emissions. The implementation of such systems can also lead to a substantial decrease in greenhouse gas emissions that are detrimental to our environment.",{"type":112,"attrs":2965,"content":2966},{"textAlign":2537},[2967,2971],{"text":2968,"type":75,"marks":2969},"Labor cost savings",[2970],{"type":710},{"text":2972,"type":75}," represent one of the most compelling financial advantages of automation. Manual gate operations typically require 2-3 security personnel per shift to handle vehicle inspections, paperwork verification, and access control. You can eliminate these positions or redeploy staff to higher-value activities when implementing automated solutions. The average facility saves $150,000-$300,000 annually in direct labor costs, with payback periods often occurring within 18-24 months.",{"type":69,"attrs":2974,"content":2975},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[2976],{"text":2977,"type":75,"marks":2978},"Scalability and Performance Advantages",[2979],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2981,"content":2982},{"textAlign":2537},[2983,2987],{"text":2984,"type":75,"marks":2985},"Scalable gate operations",[2986],{"type":710},{"text":2988,"type":75}," become critical as logistics facilities experience varying traffic volumes throughout the day. Peak hours can see 300% increases in vehicle arrivals compared to off-peak times. Intelligent gate systems adapt automatically to these fluctuations without requiring additional staffing or infrastructure modifications. The technology handles surge capacity through:",{"type":1544,"content":2990},[2991,3002,3013,3024],{"type":1547,"content":2992},[2993],{"type":112,"attrs":2994,"content":2995},{"textAlign":139},[2996,3000],{"text":2997,"type":75,"marks":2998},"Dynamic lane allocation",[2999],{"type":710},{"text":3001,"type":75}," based on real-time traffic patterns",{"type":1547,"content":3003},[3004],{"type":112,"attrs":3005,"content":3006},{"textAlign":139},[3007,3011],{"text":3008,"type":75,"marks":3009},"Automated queue management",[3010],{"type":710},{"text":3012,"type":75}," to prevent bottlenecks",{"type":1547,"content":3014},[3015],{"type":112,"attrs":3016,"content":3017},{"textAlign":139},[3018,3022],{"text":3019,"type":75,"marks":3020},"Predictive scheduling",[3021],{"type":710},{"text":3023,"type":75}," using historical data analysis",{"type":1547,"content":3025},[3026],{"type":112,"attrs":3027,"content":3028},{"textAlign":139},[3029,3033],{"text":3030,"type":75,"marks":3031},"Load balancing",[3032],{"type":710},{"text":3034,"type":75}," across multiple entry points",{"type":69,"attrs":3036,"content":3037},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[3038],{"text":3039,"type":75,"marks":3040},"Integration Complexities",[3041],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3043,"content":3044},{"textAlign":2537},[3045,3049],{"text":3046,"type":75,"marks":3047},"System integration challenges",[3048],{"type":710},{"text":3050,"type":75}," pose significant obstacles when connecting gate automation with existing warehouse management systems (WMS), transportation management systems (TMS), and yard management systems (YMS). Legacy platforms often lack modern APIs, creating data silos that prevent seamless information flow. You'll encounter compatibility issues with older database structures, inconsistent data formats, and varying communication protocols.",{"type":112,"attrs":3052,"content":3053},{"textAlign":2537},[3054],{"text":3055,"type":75},"Common integration hurdles include:",{"type":1544,"content":3057},[3058,3069,3080,3091],{"type":1547,"content":3059},[3060],{"type":112,"attrs":3061,"content":3062},{"textAlign":139},[3063,3067],{"text":3064,"type":75,"marks":3065},"Data synchronization delays",[3066],{"type":710},{"text":3068,"type":75}," between gate systems and backend platforms",{"type":1547,"content":3070},[3071],{"type":112,"attrs":3072,"content":3073},{"textAlign":139},[3074,3078],{"text":3075,"type":75,"marks":3076},"Authentication conflicts",[3077],{"type":710},{"text":3079,"type":75}," when multiple systems require different security protocols",{"type":1547,"content":3081},[3082],{"type":112,"attrs":3083,"content":3084},{"textAlign":139},[3085,3089],{"text":3086,"type":75,"marks":3087},"Real-time communication gaps",[3088],{"type":710},{"text":3090,"type":75}," that create visibility blind spots",{"type":1547,"content":3092},[3093],{"type":112,"attrs":3094,"content":3095},{"textAlign":139},[3096,3100],{"text":3097,"type":75,"marks":3098},"Customization requirements",[3099],{"type":710},{"text":3101,"type":75}," for facility-specific workflows",{"type":69,"attrs":3103,"content":3104},{"level":1752,"textAlign":2537},[3105],{"text":3106,"type":75,"marks":3107},"Training and Implementation Success Factors",[3108],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3110,"content":3111},{"textAlign":2537},[3112,3114,3117],{"text":3113,"type":75},"Staff training programs determine the success or failure of ",{"text":2530,"type":75,"marks":3115},[3116],{"type":710},{"text":3118,"type":75}," deployments. Your security team, yard operators, and IT personnel need comprehensive education on new technologies and workflows. Effective training programs span 4-6 weeks and include hands-on practice with actual equipment, troubleshooting scenarios, and emergency procedures.",{"type":112,"attrs":3120,"content":3121},{"textAlign":2537},[3122],{"text":3123,"type":75},"Training components should address system monitoring, basic maintenance tasks, exception handling, and integration with existing security protocols. You'll find that facilities investing in thorough training programs achieve 40% faster adoption rates and experience 60% fewer operational disruptions during the transition period.",{"type":112,"attrs":3125,"content":3126},{"textAlign":2537},[3127],{"text":3128,"type":75},"In conclusion, while the transition to automated gate systems presents certain challenges such as integration complexities and the need for extensive staff training, the long-term benefits far outweigh these hurdles. The potential for significant cost savings, improved operational efficiency, scalability during",{"type":69,"attrs":3130,"content":3131},{"level":138,"textAlign":2537},[3132],{"text":3133,"type":75,"marks":3134},"Conclusion",[3135],{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3137,"content":3138},{"textAlign":2537},[3139,3141,3144,3146,3150],{"text":3140,"type":75},"Implementing a ",{"text":2530,"type":75,"marks":3142},[3143],{"type":710},{"text":3145,"type":75}," is a smart investment for improving your facility's operations. The ",{"text":3147,"type":75,"marks":3148},"gate automation benefits summary",[3149],{"type":710},{"text":3151,"type":75}," shows how these advanced solutions can turn regular entry points into valuable areas for collecting data and enhancing security, resulting in a clear return on investment.",{"type":112,"attrs":3153,"content":3154},{"textAlign":2537},[3155],{"text":3156,"type":75},"It's time to stop seeing your yard gates as just barriers when they have the potential to be key control points for your entire operation. With modern gate automation systems, you can gain the visibility, control, and efficiency needed for your logistics network while also preparing for future growth.",{"type":112,"attrs":3158,"content":3159},{"textAlign":2537},[3160],{"text":3161,"type":75},"The technology is available now to eliminate manual delays, lower operational costs, and create a smooth process that meets your customers' expectations. Your next step is to assess how intelligent gate automation fits into your overall plan for digitizing your yard and choose solutions that work well with your current infrastructure.",{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[3164],"89f3c339-f4ad-4593-accc-39e8eebbfc7d","A gate automation system is a technology that turns traditional manual entry points into smart, self-operating access controls. It combines hardware like automated barriers, sensors, and cameras with advanced software to manage vehicle and personnel entry without the need for human involvement.",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":3167},{},"Gate Automation Systems: Boost Yard Security & Efficiency Today",{"id":3170,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":3171,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":3172,"is_external_url":49},92149461647658,"/storyblok/f/337048/1856x1192/e0e9c40a04/u.webp",{},[],"Discover how gate automation systems enhance yard security and operational efficiency—accelerating check-ins, reducing human error, and providing real-time visibility at every access point.",{"value":2028,"plugin":2454},"gate-automation-systems-boost-security-efficien